snippet: President Viktor F. Yanukovich freed a number of political prisoners on Sunday, but kept former Prime Minister Yulia V. Tymoshenko in custody.
abstract: Ukraine's Pres Viktor F Yanukovich pardons Yuri V Lutsenko, country’s second-most-prominent political prisoner, but keeps his biggest rival, former prime minister Yulia V Tymoshenko, in custody.
lead_paragraph: President Viktor F. Yanukovich freed a number of political prisoners on Sunday, but kept former Prime Minister Yulia V. Tymoshenko in custody.

headline.main: Ukraine President Frees a Rival’s Allies, but Leaves Her in Prison
headline.print_headline: Ukraine President Frees a Rival’s Allies, but Leaves Her in Prison
